text: 223 Main Street is a historic commercial building located in downtown Evansville, Indiana. It was built in 1910, and is a three-story, Art Nouveau style building. Note: This includes , , and Accompanying photographs It was listed on the National Register of Historic Places in 1982. The building is currently home to River City Mercantile & Coffee Co. ==References== Category:Commercial buildings on the National Register of Historic Places in Indiana Category:Art Nouveau architecture in Indiana Category:Commercial buildings completed in 1910 Category:Buildings and structures in Evansville, Indiana Category:National Register of Historic Places in Evansville, Indiana
